%e A322384 The 6 permutations of {1,2,3} are:
%e A322384   (1)     (2) (3)
%e A322384   (1,2)   (3)
%e A322384   (1,3)   (2)
%e A322384   (2,3)   (1)
%e A322384   (1,2,3)
%e A322384   (1,3,2)
%e A322384 so there are 13 elements in the first cycles, 4 in the second cycles and only 1 in the third cycles.
